WEBVTT

00:00:12.074 --> 00:00:21.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Life had changed for Naomi,
For she had lost her sons.

00:00:21.834 --> 00:00:31.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Though Ruth was sad, she comforted
Naomi with her love.

00:00:31.802 --> 00:00:41.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ruth truly was a friend
On whom Naomi could depend.

00:00:41.729 --> 00:00:51.447 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ruth said when needed most:
“Where you go I will go.”

00:00:53.824 --> 00:00:58.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Where you go I will go.”

00:00:59.371 --> 00:01:09.423 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They stuck together side by side,
Living for the truth.

00:01:09.423 --> 00:01:18.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah saw and blessed the love
That was shown by Ruth.

00:01:18.974 --> 00:01:29.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is so much to learn from them,
Like how to be a loyal friend.

00:01:29.026 --> 00:01:38.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These words I will echo:
“Where you go I will go.”

00:01:38.243 --> 00:01:43.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When my friends are sad,
I’ll stick to them.

00:01:43.207 --> 00:01:46.043 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s when I’m needed most.

00:01:47.628 --> 00:01:53.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ll be a shoulder to cry on,
Someone to rely on.

00:01:53.384 --> 00:01:56.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ll be a true friend.

00:02:01.558 --> 00:02:06.188 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Where you go I will go.”

